abstract: CHICAGO, Sept. 4.--George Holland, of Evergreen, Montcalm County, Mich., was killed by melon thieves last night. He heard them in his garden, and taking a shot gun chased them out. abstract: NORWICH, Sept. 7.--A single flash of lightning last Summer struck an entire potato field of several acres belonging to N.J. Wood, of North Sterling, in Windham County. abstract: KINGSTON, N.Y., Sept. 11.--William Stevens, aged about 50 years, was driving down Clove Mountain, one of the steepest of the Shawangunk range, near Alligerville, yesterday, with five tons of millstone on his wagon. He leaves a wife and family.

abstract: TOWANDA, Penn., Sept. 24.--Bartholomew Lane and E. Decker, partners in the livery business here, had an altercation yesterday. Decker knocked Lane down. abstract: BRANFORD, Conn., Sept. 29.--The general store of John Hutchinson, on Main-street, was entered by burglars last night and $2,500 worth of goods taken. Entrance was effected by breaking in one of the panels of the back door. The burglars left behind them a chisel and bit, together with a sandbag. The store contains nearly $20,000 worth of goods. No clue to the thieves.
